content: It is nice to see so many of you here.
Also, welcome to our guests. hopefully they enjoy watching our class
The most recent even in the world's renju has been the Russian Championship Final.
It ended some days ago, and Konstantin Chingin became the master of Russia.
The second place was achieved by Vlad Kareev
but this is not High Leaague in Russia

Sushkov and Sinyov did not take part

russian high league is the russian championship
and that is what I am telling about
we cannot say that WC is not top tournament just because Nakamura didnot take part in it
the final of russian championship is called "high league"
the tournament that just ended was the high league of russia
indeed, some top players such as Sinyov and Sushkov did not join it,
ok, now i see the definitions
but all the other best players were all there.

but the rest of them are all under 30
Kozhin did not, as I remember
Today we will study the game from that tournament,
Because of the round robin system,
the match between main rivals may happen anytime,
So it happened that they had to play with each other in quite early stage.

maybe black will be more active at the first stage, but seems hard to finish with promising result

no need to give the black the powerful k7 stone

possibility to defense on J13 without threat of 4*4?

if white attacks, then it can create many black lines with the help of 29
one of the ideas you have not mentioned is to re-activate the material of 4x4 after the white's annoying attacker was blocked
it means, with the move 29, black made the upper RIGHT area alive

which is a good tactical move
because we spoke in tactics class,
makes it harder for white to defend or?
that we will not outplay the threatened forbidden move,
if it is simply possible to eliminate the treat
by doing that, we leave ourselves more options to use these fours later
But if we waste them all at first,
we need to play to g12 anyway
and lost our useful materials that way
And playing such "waiting" move always puts the opponent into deep thinking,
because there is no obvious next move for white.
so while white is thinking now,
as I said, both were running out of time
but 3 most important ones were mentioned by strul.
Chingin felt uncomfortable about the open 4x4 point,
and he decided to use the g10 tempo,
he is slowly getting trapped on the left side,
you see white stones all inside.
and Chingin had no time to confirm,
Obviously he feared that black would take that point,
otherwise he would not have played it.
But since he had a few minutes left on his clock,
he had to make the decision without deep calculations,
what was the times controls rt?
And in such cases we often play the four even if later turns out was not necessary.
I dont have the exact information of their total time, or bayomi condition.
I just know from Kareev that both players had time trouble.
Moves 41 and 43 - clear signs of time-trouble.
Amazing, in such a short time, Chingin is still making good defense moves.
he was just about to fight is way out of all the troubles,

and also it was too early to develop for white,
because black was having an initiative still.
